        <note resp="Philip Lampi">"On the same evening General Adair resigned, and on Wednesday the legislature proceeded to elect another senator to serve until the 2nd of March next; for which period the General was elected last season. Henry Clay, esq. was chosen by a large majority. The votes were; for Henry Clay, 58, George M. Bibb, 10, John Pope, 1." The Palladium (Frankfort, KY).  November 20, 1806.</note>
        <note resp="Philip Lampi">Henry Clay was elected even though he did not meet the constitutionally required age of 30.  Clay would not turn 30 until April 12, 1807 - after his term was over.</note>
